BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260203T150000Z
DTEND:20260203T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260203T000000Z
SUMMARY:Looking Slowly at Early Modern Maps
DESCRIPTION:Maps are incredibly rich documents that only reveal some of 
 their secrets after slow and deliberate study\, and it is precisely this 
 aspect of maps that we will explore in this two-hour workshop. Chet Van 
 Duzer will analyze several early modern maps and provide examples of 
 important characteristics of them that can only be appreciated and 
 understood through slow looking. He will also supply advice on how to study 
 maps slowly\, and workshop participants will consult facsimiles of early 
 modern maps to begin to practice looking slowly at them\, with plenty of 
 time for examining the maps together and asking questions. The goal of the 
 workshop is that participants will gain experience and tools for engaging 
 more fully with maps in the future.\n\n\n\nSpeaker Bio: \n\nChet Van Duzer 
 is a board member of the Lazarus Project at the University of Rochester\, 
 which brings multispectral imaging to cultural institutions around the 
 world—he directs the projects relating to maps and globes. He has 
 published extensively on medieval and Renaissance maps\; his book Frames 
 that Speak: Cartouches on Early Modern Maps was recently published by Brill 
 in Open Access. His current projects are a book about self-portraits by 
 cartographers that appear on maps\, a book about the historical cartography 
 of the Indian Ocean\, and a book about images of terrestrial animals and 
 birds on maps.
LOCATION:Hazelbaker Hall (Wells E159)
ORGANIZER;CN="Theresa Quill":MAILTO:theward@iu.edu
CATEGORIES:CartoShop: Workshops on Digital Mapping
UID:LibCal-1228-16110599
URL:https://iub.libcal.com/event/16110599
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260204T170000Z
DTEND:20260204T183000Z
DTSTAMP:20260204T000000Z
SUMMARY:Center for Survey Research Consultations
DESCRIPTION:Make an appointment now! 
 https://iub.libcal.com/appointments/csr\n\nYou have the option to schedule 
 on Zoom or in-person.\n\nThe Center for Survey Research consults with 
 faculty\, staff\, and students across a wide range of substantive 
 disciplines spanning business\, education\, the social sciences\, and the 
 health sciences. We are happy to assist with any qualitative or 
 quantitative research project by providing consultation on:\n research 
 design\n questionnaire development and review\n sample design\n online 
 interface and reporting portal development\n database and data collection 
 instrument programming including Qualtrics online survey software\n 
 usability testing\n sample management including high-volume email 
 campaigns\n data collection using online\, telephone\, mail\, and 
 face-to-face administration\n qualitative methods (semi-structured 
 interviews\, focus groups\, observations\, etc.)\n data processing\n data 
 analysis\n\nTakes place in the Wells Library Scholars' Commons\, first 
 floor of the east tower. No question too big or too small!
ORGANIZER;CN="CSR Center for Survey Research":MAILTO:afbowers@iu.edu
CATEGORIES:Scholars' Commons Consulting
UID:LibCal-1228-16110420
URL:https://iub.libcal.com/calendar/workshops/csr
END:VEVENT
